<br />
The Moria Scam by Jared Souer    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">OK, this is the Free Peoples strategy.  I usually bid 2-3 burdens to start off, hoping to play Gandalf&#39;s Cart.  If not, I have most of the starting companions to play from my draw deck.  I usually move 1 time a turn, tryng to just stay alive, letting my shadow hand do the work.  I know I have only 1 copie of most of my cards, this is because I own only 1 copie of these cards and like what they do.<br />
<br />
For the Shadow side, I use the awsome Moria Orcs to try to overwhelm my opponent with their little twilight cost.  I have the Watcher in the Water combo because most of the time it does lots of damage and the Balrog&#39;s toys because of the same reason.  <br />
<br />
That&#39;s the strategy.  Hope you like my deck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
